According to the regulations, the Cosmetics, Devices and Drugs Authority shall prepare a register of every registered cosmetic and enter the following particulars: 
(a) the name of the cosmetic; 
(b) the name of the manufacturer; 
(c) the country of manufacture; 
(d) the registration number assigned to it; 
(e) the name and address of the holder of the certificate of registration; 
(f) whether he is an importer or manufacturer; and 
(g) the number of the licence issued to him (Source: cdd_regulations_05.pdf, Page 1). 

Additionally, the licensed manufacturer of cosmetics shall provide information as required by the Authority, inform the Authority of any material alterations, and keep records of manufacture available for inspection (Source: NMRA_cdd_regulations_05.pdf, Page 5).

The registration rules for cosmetics are outlined in the Cosmetics, Devices and Drugs Act, No. 27 of 1980, as amended by Act, No. 38 of 1984. According to the regulations, every cosmetic shall be called a "registered cosmetic" (Source: cdd_regulations_05.pdf, Page 1). 

The Cosmetics, Devices and Drugs Authority shall prepare a register of every registered cosmetic, which shall include the following particulars: 
(a) the name of the cosmetic; 
(b) the name of the manufacturer; 
(c) the country of manufacture; 
(d) the registration number assigned to it; 
(e) the name and address of the holder of the certificate of registration; 
(f) whether he is an importer or manufacturer; and 
(g) the number of the licence issued to him (Source: cdd_regulations_05.pdf, Page 1).

The application for registration of a cosmetic by a manufacturer should be made using the Application Form for Registration of a Cosmetic by a Manufacturer (Form C Regulation 4 (5)) (Source: cdd_regulations_05.pdf, Page 8). 

The registration process begins after the expiry of a period of three months from the date of operation, which is January 1, 1986 (Source: cdd_regulations_05.pdf, Page 1).
